                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18480403-1053-offence-1 t18480403-name-421"></join>James Drewett</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-422" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-422" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-422" type="surname" value="MILLS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-422" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD MILLS.</persName>
                  </hi> I live at Chapel-place, Long lane, Southwark. I work for James Drewett, of the Spur Inn—he had a dark-brown mare to take care</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184804030044"></xptr>
               <p>of—I do not know whose it was—it was safe when I shut the stable-door, between eight and nine o'clock on 3rd March—I missed it about ten—there was not lock on the door—the prisoner lived at the Nag's 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—I have seen it since, in charge of the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-423" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-423" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-423" type="surname" value="HAYNES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-423" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HAYNES.</persName>
                  </hi> I am waterman at the Spur. I saw the mare brought there twenty weeks ago—I do not know who by—it was lost last Friday night.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-424" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-424" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-424" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-424" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL WHITE.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a horse-slaughterer at Thomas-street, Whitechapel. About nine o'clock last Friday night, the prisoner brought the mare, and asked if I would'buy it—I said, "Yes," and asked how much he wanted—he said 30<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I said I would give him 27<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he said I should have it if I would give him a drop of gin—he said it was an old favourite, and the wanted it killed—I said I could not do that, as I was obliged to give the inspector twelve hour's notice—I did not think it ought to be salughtered, I detained it, and gave it and him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-425" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-425" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-425" type="surname" value="GUY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-425" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>BENJAMIN GUY.</persName>
                  </hi> On Friday night, 3rd March, I went with the prisoner and the mare, by my master's orders, to Long-lane—the prisoner tapped me on the shoulder, and said, "It is no use, my friend, going any further, for I have stole the horse myself from the Spur, in the Borough"—I took him and the mare back to my master—he sent for the police.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-426" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-426" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-426" type="surname" value="MERRITT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-426" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES MERRITT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) About twelve o'clock on Friday night Guy fetched me to Mr. White's—I found the prisoner and the mare there—White gave them into my charge—I took them to the station.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> A man asked me to take it to Whitechapel, and sell it, and told me what to say; and was to give me 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; I did not steal it.</p>
